.\"", "\"ROLLING BUDGET APPROACH\":\"A rolling budget approach involves continuously updating the budget to reflect changes in the business environment. This approach requires frequent updates and adjustments to the budget, which can be facilitated by training programs and integrated information systems.\"", "\"TRAINING PROGRAMS\":\"Training programs for sales managers and finance staff are essential to ensure the smooth implementation of the rolling budget approach. These programs will improve their knowledge and reduce resistance to change.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE MEASURES\":\"Performance measures should be adjusted to reflect the new rolling budget system. This includes setting realistic targets that reflect the current economic environment and spreading targets more evenly throughout the year to improve staff motivation.\"", "\"ROLLING BUDGET IMPLEMENTATION\":\"Rolling budget implementation should involve staff consultation, cost-benefit analysis, and measures to avoid disruption to productivity or morale.\"", "\"EVALUATING DECISION PACKAGES AND ZBB TRANSITION FOR PLAINFIELD COUNTY PUBLIC AUTHORITY LIBRARY\":\"Plainfield County Public Authority (PCPA) has transitioned from incremental budgeting to zero-based budgeting (ZBB). The library manager is considering two decision packages for computer upgrades to respond to criticism of the library being old-fashioned. The decision packages include costs for staff, IS maintenance, and website hosting, with varying impacts on library operations and costs.\"", "\"DECISION PACKAGE 1: COMPUTER UPGRADE\":\"This decision package involves replacing only the computers at a total cost of $45,000. Annual IS maintenance costs will fall to $9,000, while annual website costs and staff costs will remain constant. This upgrade will not substantially change library operations.\"", "\"DECISION PACKAGE 2: COMPUTER UPGRADE AND INTEGRATED LIBRARY SYSTEM\":\"This decision package involves purchasing new computers plus additional hardware and software to automate core library processes at a total cost of $98,500. It will allow self-service borrowing of books, reduce staff members to four, increase annual IS maintenance costs to $22,000, and increase annual website costs to $3,000.\"", "\"DECISION PACKAGE 2\":\"Decision package 2 involves a computer upgrade including an integrated library system costing $98,500, annual IS maintenance costs of $22,000, website hosting costs of $3,000, and staff costs of $112,000, totaling $235,500 for the first year.\"", "\"ADVANTAGES OF ZBB\":\"Advantages of ZBB include a focus on the objectives and needs of the community, evaluation of decision packages by value for money, involvement of the library manager in the budgeting process, and identification of operational efficiencies and quality improvements.\"", "\"DISADVANTAGES OF ZBB\":\"Disadvantages of ZBB include being time-consuming for the library manager, potential distraction from other important responsibilities, and a focus on short-term objectives over long-term benefits.\"", "\"CAPACITY ANALYSIS AND PRODUCTION EFFICIENCY FOR TOY CO\":\"Toy Co is a small company manufacturing toys for toddlers and children, facing increasing overhead costs and loss of key customers due to shipping errors and missed delivery dates. The management accountant is considering introducing activity-based budgeting to improve efficiency and reduce costs.\"", "\"QUALITY INSPECTION TIME\":\"QUALITY INSPECTION TIME\" refers to the time required to inspect the quality of products. For Toy Co, this time is specifically 15 hours per batch. Additionally, quality inspection time encompasses the total hours required to inspect batches within a quarter, which can serve as an indicator of whether the department is operating below or above capacity.", "\"PACKAGING AND SHIPPING TIME\":\"PACKAGING AND SHIPPING TIME\" refers to the time required to package and ship products. For Toy Co, this time is specifically 1 hour per order. Additionally, \"PACKAGING AND SHIPPING TIME\" can also denote the total hours required to complete the shipment of orders within a quarter. This metric can be used to determine whether there is a shortage or surplus of available hours for packaging and shipping activities."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}